<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=719&amp;p=6204#p6204</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=719&amp;p=6204#p6204"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[regarding mmc5 sound]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=719&amp;p=6204#p6204"><![CDATA[
At 1.79 MHz, any wave with fewer than about 81 clocks per cycle will be inaudible (above 22 kHz). If my calculation is right, a raw period of 4 or less will be above 22 kHz (4 results in timer period of 4*2+2=10, and wave period of 10*8=80).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Thu Nov 03, 2005 12:08 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
